{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66446704970e6e9ab542cf6b", "type": "numerical", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTA", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba5"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "664466ee278297dee60eda68", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A hydrogen atom changes its state from $n=3$ to $n=2$. Due to recoil, the percentage change in the wave length of emitted light is approximately $1 \\times 10^{-n}$. The value of $n$ is_____. \n[Given $\\mathrm{Rhc}=13.6 \\mathrm{eV}, \\mathrm{hc}=1242 \\mathrm{eV} \\mathrm{nm}, \\mathrm{h}=6.6 \\times 10^{-34} \\mathrm{~J} \\mathrm{~s}$ mass of the hydrogenatom $=1.6 \\times 10^{-27} \\mathrm{~kg}$ ]", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "7", "solution": {"text": "$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\Delta \\mathrm{E}=13.6\\left(\\frac{1}{2^2}-\\frac{1}{3^2}\\right)=1.9 \\mathrm{eV} \\\\\n& \\Delta \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda} \\\\\n& \\lambda=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\Delta \\mathrm{E}} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{i}}=\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{t}} \\\\\n& 0=-\\mathrm{mv}+\\frac{\\mathrm{h}}{\\lambda^{\\prime \\prime}} \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{v}=\\frac{\\mathrm{h}}{\\mathrm{m} \\lambda^{\\prime}} \\\\\n& \\Delta \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{mv^{2 }}+\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda^{\\prime \\prime}} \\\\\n& =\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{h}}{\\mathrm{m} \\lambda^{\\prime}}\\right)^2+\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda^{\\prime}}\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Now\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\Delta \\mathrm{E}=\\frac{h^2}{2 \\mathrm{~m} \\lambda^{\\prime^2}}+\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda^{\\prime}} \\\\\n& \\lambda^{\\prime 2} \\Delta \\mathrm{E}-\\mathrm{hc} \\lambda^{\\prime}-\\frac{\\mathrm{h}^2}{2 \\mathrm{~m}}=0 \\\\\n& \\lambda^{\\prime}=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc} \\pm \\sqrt{\\mathrm{h}^2 \\mathrm{c}^2+\\frac{4 \\Delta \\mathrm{Eh}^2}{2 \\mathrm{~m}}}}{2 \\Delta \\mathrm{E}} \\\\\n& \\lambda^{\\prime}=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc} \\pm \\mathrm{hc} \\sqrt{1+\\frac{2 \\Delta \\mathrm{E}}{\\mathrm{mc}}}}{2 \\Delta \\mathrm{E}}\n\\end{aligned}$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{\\lambda^{\\prime}}{\\lambda}=\\frac{1+\\left(1+\\frac{2 \\Delta \\mathrm{E}}{\\mathrm{mc}^2}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{2}}}{2}=\\frac{1+1+\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{E}}{\\mathrm{mc}^2}}{2} \\\\\n& \\frac{\\lambda^{\\prime}}{\\lambda}=1+\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{E}}{2 \\mathrm{mc}^2} \\\\\n& \\frac{\\lambda^{\\prime}-\\lambda}{\\lambda}=\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{E}}{2 \\mathrm{mc}^2}=\\frac{1.9 \\times 1.6 \\times 10^{-19}}{2 \\times 1.67 \\times 10^{-27} \\times 9 \\times 10^{15}}=10^{-9} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\% \\text { change } \\approx 10^{-7}\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Correct answer 7", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "111a0fa27ce642938ea58ebf7f51f838", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/0U4ptJbj3RIAE.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/0U4ptJbj3RIAE.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Main (Imp. PYQs from 2023 - 2019)"}, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ68223288", "syllabusStatus": "No Change", "numericalLowerLimit": 7, "numericalUpperLimit": 7, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4